>
  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">How Customer Offers Work</h2>
  <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-4">When you place cooked meat on a serving table, customers appear one by one and make purchase offers. Each offer is a random price within a range based on the meat's value and your table tier.</p>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8">Offer Evaluation Tips</h2>
  <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-8">
    <li>• <strong>Know your meat values</strong> — Check our <a href="/meat-values/" class="text-orange-500 underline">Meat Values page</a> so you recognize when an offer is good or bad.</li>
    <li>• <strong>Decline fast</strong> — Don't hold up your table waiting for a great offer. A decent offer now is better than waiting 30 seconds for a slightly better one.</li>
    <li>• <strong>Use Auto Sell</strong> — Once you buy the Auto Sell upgrade, you can set a threshold and let the system handle offers automatically.</li>
    <li>• <strong>Premium tables boost everything</strong> — The +10% and +20% offer value bonuses from upgraded tables apply to all offers, making even "bad" offers decent.</li>
  </ul>
</ArticleLayout>
